<paragraph blockId="29.[192,1440,1744,1929]" lastBlockId="30.[192,1441,217,370]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="29" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,342,1744,1768]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Definition.</emphasis>
Unexpectedly, a relative of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scudder, 1872" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1872" box="[711,1063,1744,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Amblyscirtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[711,871,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Amblyscirtes</emphasis>
Scudder, 1872
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[1083,1138,1745,1769]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Edwards, 1862" authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vialis">
<emphasis box="[1249,1440,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Hesperia vialis</emphasis>
Edwards, 1862
</taxonomicName>
) and is sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hemming, 1939" authorityName="Hemming" authorityYear="1939" box="[575,876,1776,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Remella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,675,1776,1800]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Remella</emphasis>
Hemming, 1939
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[892,946,1777,1801]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1798" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[1045,1432,1776,1801]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="remus">
<emphasis box="[1045,1235,1777,1800]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Hesperia remus</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1798
</taxonomicName>
) with 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1901]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" box="[253,574,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mnasicles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,374,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Mnasicles</emphasis>
Godman, [1901]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[588,642,1809,1833]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, 1901" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" box="[740,1101,1808,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Mnasicles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="geta">
<emphasis box="[740,918,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Mnasicles geta</emphasis>
Godman, 1901
</taxonomicName>
), which all are in a different subtribe (Moncina) from 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[489,832,1840,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Paratrytone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,633,1841,1864]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Paratrytone</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[845,898,1841,1865]" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Godman, 1900" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[995,1431,1840,1865]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Paratrytone" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhexenor">
<emphasis box="[995,1251,1840,1864]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Paratrytone rhexenor</emphasis>
Godman, 1900
</taxonomicName>
) (in Hesperiina) where this lineage was placed previously (
<figureCitation box="[880,1009,1872,1897]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="28">Fig. 11–12</figureCitation>
). Distinguished from its relatives by sacculus about as long as vinculum with tegumen in lateral view, valva simple, nearly diamond-shaped with vary narrow harpe ending in a point directed dorsoposteriad and not separated from ampulla, very long antennae reaching apical spots near costa, all (except the small cell spot) forewing spots forming a continuous line (separated by black veins only) and most spots in a line on ventral hindwing. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly28779.8.7:T461C, aly577.34.1:C115G, aly1370.21.5:A2861G, aly531.10.5:G517C, aly2124.3.99:A3193G.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,1320,394,418]" box="[192,1320,394,418]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,394,418]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a masculine noun in the nominative singular, for the 
<typeStatus box="[1165,1218,394,418]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,707,441,466]" box="[192,707,441,466]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,432,441,465]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Species included.</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus box="[553,606,442,466]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[192,823,490,514]" box="[192,823,490,514]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,380,490,514]" pageId="30" pageNumber="29">Parent taxon.</emphasis>
Subtribe Moncina A. 
<bibRefCitation author="Warren, A. D. &amp; J. R. Ogawa &amp; A. V. Z. Brower" box="[647,819,490,514]" journalOrPublisher="Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics" pageId="30" pageNumber="29" pagination="642 - 676" part="24" refId="ref28580" refString="Warren, A. D., J. R. Ogawa, and A. V. Z. Brower. 2008. Phylogenetic relationships of subfamilies and circumscription of tribes in the family Hesperiidae (Lepidoptera: Hesperioidea). Cladistics 24 (5): 642 - 676." type="journal article" year="2008">Warren, 2008</bibRefCitation>
